						<summary>

						<p>Slab (another) in survey No. 298, adjacent to the Śāmbaśiva temple.</p>						

						<p>Rēnāṭi chōḷa; [Manu] chōḷa.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 9th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>The record begins with the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of Aridurdharavara etc., and registers a grant of <hi rend="italic">Pannasa</hi> land of fifty <hi rend="italic">maṟutus</hi> extent yielding a <hi rend="italic">siddhāya</hi> of 15 gold <hi rend="italic">rūkas</hi> and 7 <hi rend="italic">puṭṭis</hi> of other land at Vēlpucheṟuvu to Mēyi Bhaṭlu by Kalichōḷa, the son (Maganṟu) and by one Vaḷabhāya on the occasion of solar eclipse.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">Inscriptions of Andhra Pradesh; Cuddapah Dist.</hi> Part-I, pp 132 ff.]</p>						

						</summary>
